data.description: Turn Key, Stucco Duplex on third-acre lot, in Old Town Monument. Enjoy 4th July Parade, Monument Lake (fishing, paddle boarding, kayaking ) walk to great restaurants, coffee shops, breweries, and groceries. Santa Fe Trail at the end of the street.AFA Northgate is 10 minutes away. New roof coming,new(er) hot water heaters replaced last year and this year.Furnace cleaned and inspected. No HOA.  Units are mirror images of each other. 3 spacious bedrooms in each unit. Back yard fully fenced with wooden privacy fencing. Each unit has its own fully fenced backyard, patio area. Two storage sheds. Unit B ,garage was transformed into a flex space( remodeled to a fully functioning room that could be used as an office, Living room, Studio,or Exercise room. Let your imagination run wild! /Can be accessed from inside the home or  French doors grant access from outside.( Flex room easily reverts back to being a garage )  Loads of parking in the driveway. The lot could fit another similar size duplex.(buyer to verify) Crawl space (4' under each unit) space for storage.*Unit A Main bedroom and bathroom no photos at this time. Flex room Unit B no photos at this time, total square footage does not include flex room conversion *Average rent is an estimate as units were never rentals
